						               													<description>User summary&amp;#10;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#158;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#184;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#167;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170; (Majori) is a party game with a werewolf style of play. Players are given two options, and everyone pretends to be in support of the majority choice. But if a player is not convincing enough, they might be voted out as a minority supporter. If the player was actually a majority supporter, all minority supporters win. If the player was a minority supporter, the one with the most votes loses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Open the theme (exampe: A. Coke B. Pepsi).&amp;#10;     Which do you like? Place your card (A or B) face down.&amp;#10;     Shuffle the cards &amp;amp; Open them up.&amp;#10;     A minority must not exist in this world.&amp;#10;     Everyone defends the Majority choice.&amp;#10;     If you are minority, you pretend to be majority.&amp;#10;     Everyone thinks about who is minority.&amp;#10;     Ready, set, go! We point toward the person you estimated as minority.&amp;#10;     We will open the card of the person with the most votes.&amp;#10;     Result:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;He is a majority : minority win&amp;#10;He is a minority : person with most votes lose&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
